race.comment: BLAZE (8) hit the ground running and never headed to claim a maiden victory two back then finished a 8 length seventh last start at Healesville over 300m (16.96). Returns to the scene of her maiden win. Look for sharp improvement here. GRAFFITI (3) is rarely out of the finish, recording six places from 11 starts. Better run when finding the frame last time though, finishing second (22.60) at Ballarat. Comes out of a solid form race last start. Hard to beat again. BAROOGA QUEEN (1) flew the lids last start and led throughout to register her maiden win by half a length at Bendigo over 425m (24.29). Boxed well here. Harder here but expected to feature again. BLACKPOOL LOTTIE (5) scored by 4.5 lengths last time (22.58) in a Maiden over 390m at Ballarat. Has already won out of this draw.
